  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 13.23,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.85,
      "end": 34.34,
      "text": "영화 감상과 영어 공부를 동시에 일석이조."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.6,
      "end": 36.04,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬 타임."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.04,
      "end": 40.0,
      "text": "10월에는 A Breathtaking and Wondrous Movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.48,
      "end": 41.78,
      "text": "The Secret Garden."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.96,
      "end": 43.58,
      "text": "Well, good morning, Chris."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.88,
      "end": 44.44,
      "text": "Good morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.74,
      "end": 45.8,
      "text": "좀 전에 그건 뭐예요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.24,
      "end": 48.0,
      "text": "That was a, it was so breathtaking."
    },
    {
      "start": 48.22,
      "end": 51.76,
      "text": "Your introduction was breathtaking that I had to, you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.86,
      "end": 53.16,
      "text": "just take a deep breath."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.42,
      "end": 55.5,
      "text": "역시 센스가 있으세요, 그죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.04,
      "end": 59.46,
      "text": "정말 breathtaking하고 Wondrous Movie가 맞는 것 같습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.9,
      "end": 60.14,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.54,
      "end": 63.64,
      "text": "And let me tell you a little bit about the background of this film."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.84,
      "end": 64.36,
      "text": "Please do."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.46,
      "end": 64.64,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.7,
      "end": 65.08,
      "text": "Go ahead."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.08,
      "end": 65.48,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.68,
      "end": 70.0,
      "text": "It is set in England in 1947, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.2,
      "end": 71.02,
      "text": "Way back then."
    },
    {
      "start": 71.12,
      "end": 76.08,
      "text": "와, 19세기의 영국에 특히도 Yorkshire, 그 황무지,"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.36,
      "end": 78.88,
      "text": "More, 이거 배경으로 하고 있는 영화예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 78.94,
      "end": 79.28,
      "text": "More."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.52,
      "end": 80.12,
      "text": "More, 그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.3,
      "end": 81.16,
      "text": "American style."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.18,
      "end": 82.56,
      "text": "American style pronunciation."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.02,
      "end": 86.16,
      "text": "근데 이제 Yorkshire이라는 단어를 저는 항상 들을 때마다요."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.28,
      "end": 89.42,
      "text": "It always reminds me of a certain species of dogs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.52,
      "end": 90.64,
      "text": "such as Yorkshire Terrier."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.82,
      "end": 91.46,
      "text": "The Terriers."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.6,
      "end": 91.98,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.98,
      "end": 95.16,
      "text": "I always think of two things when I hear Yorkshire."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.9,
      "end": 96.94,
      "text": "Yorkshire Terriers."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.08,
      "end": 97.2,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.32,
      "end": 98.46,
      "text": "And Yorkshire Pudding."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.04,
      "end": 100.38,
      "text": "There's a very famous pudding."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.56,
      "end": 100.92,
      "text": "Yeah, 맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.06,
      "end": 103.04,
      "text": "Peter 씨가 옛날에 한번 이야기해 준 적 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.08,
      "end": 103.36,
      "text": "Did he?"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.44,
      "end": 103.62,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.62,
      "end": 106.3,
      "text": "In the U.S., they call them popovers."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.7,
      "end": 107.26,
      "text": "Popovers."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.48,
      "end": 109.7,
      "text": "We have them for breakfast sometimes."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.08,
      "end": 110.6,
      "text": "Same as many."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.9,
      "end": 112.98,
      "text": "I didn't know they're from Yorkshire."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.14,
      "end": 113.48,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.48,
      "end": 115.12,
      "text": "근데 발음이 되게 독특하네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 115.38,
      "end": 115.64,
      "text": "Oh, really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 115.64,
      "end": 116.98,
      "text": "I mean, Yorkshire 이렇게 할 줄 알았는데,"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.44,
      "end": 118.1,
      "text": "Yorkshire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.52,
      "end": 122.04,
      "text": "아, 이거 약간 무식한 미국식 발음인 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.76,
      "end": 123.28,
      "text": "Yorkshire."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.76,
      "end": 124.72,
      "text": "어머나, 세상에."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.56,
      "end": 127.36,
      "text": "S-H-I-R-E."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.5,
      "end": 129.2,
      "text": "이거 누가 봐도 Shire."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.4,
      "end": 129.82,
      "text": "그러네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.9,
      "end": 131.98,
      "text": "그것만 보면 그렇게 발음할 수 있겠죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.0,
      "end": 132.92,
      "text": "이거 Yorkshire."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.16,
      "end": 133.42,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.42,
      "end": 134.68,
      "text": "두 개 가능하지 않을까."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.82,
      "end": 135.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.3,
      "end": 138.72,
      "text": "Anyway, and I remember the time when I read the novel,"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.32,
      "end": 140.44,
      "text": "Wolverine Heights."
    },
    {
      "start": 140.8,
      "end": 141.88,
      "text": "Is that correct to pronounce?"
    },
    {
      "start": 142.02,
      "end": 142.56,
      "text": "Wolverine."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.58,
      "end": 144.18,
      "text": "The title of the novel."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.48,
      "end": 145.52,
      "text": "폭풍의 언덕."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.12,
      "end": 150.7,
      "text": "W-U-T-H-E-R-I-N-G."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.6,
      "end": 152.76,
      "text": "Wolverine Heights."
    },
    {
      "start": 153.36,
      "end": 154.68,
      "text": "W-U-U-T-H-E-R-I-N-G."
    },
    {
      "start": 154.68,
      "end": 155.28,
      "text": "W-U-U-T-H-E-R-I-N-G."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.28,
      "end": 159.42,
      "text": "No, W-U-U-T-H-E-R-I-N-G."
    },
    {
      "start": 159.42,
      "end": 166.84,
      "text": "네, 어쨌든 폭풍의 언덕이라는 소설을 제목으로 안 읽으신 걸로 지금 판명이 났어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.34,
      "end": 167.7,
      "text": "알겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.3,
      "end": 168.94,
      "text": "복잡해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 169.2,
      "end": 172.64,
      "text": "제가 이 폭풍의 언덕이라는 소설도 되게 재미있게 읽었었던."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.66,
      "end": 174.14,
      "text": "W-U-T-H-E-R-I-N-G."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.38,
      "end": 175.96,
      "text": "아니요. WU-U예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.04,
      "end": 177.5,
      "text": "그래요? 안 쓰는 단어에요."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.5,
      "end": 178.86,
      "text": "그래요? 네, 미안해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 179.24,
      "end": 183.02,
      "text": "자, 폭풍의 언덕이라는 소설을 제가 어렸을 때 정말 많이 읽었었거든요."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.74,
      "end": 187.9,
      "text": "근데 제가 이 전체 스토리는 다 기억은 못해도"
    },
    {
      "start": 187.9,
      "end": 192.86,
      "text": "I just remember the moment I imagined the background or atmosphere of the book."
    },
    {
      "start": 193.42,
      "end": 196.68,
      "text": "그냥 상상 속으로 이 역실에 관련되어서"
    },
    {
      "start": 196.68,
      "end": 199.76,
      "text": "그 환경이 어땠을까, 분위기가 어땠을까"
    },
    {
      "start": 199.76,
      "end": 204.88,
      "text": "그렇게 책을 읽으면서 떠올렸던 시간이 되게 소중했던 메모리입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.88,
      "end": 208.24,
      "text": "Yorkshire. It's a beautiful, beautiful place."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.1,
      "end": 213.42,
      "text": "It's full of vast countryside, unspoiled countryside."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.2,
      "end": 216.66,
      "text": "So just very great natural settings."
    },
    {
      "start": 216.92,
      "end": 219.74,
      "text": "And famous for pudding and terriers."
    },
    {
      "start": 220.5,
      "end": 222.88,
      "text": "It's also known as God's own county."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.0,
      "end": 226.9,
      "text": "그래요? 얼마나 좋길래 그런 표현을 또 붙였을까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 227.12,
      "end": 229.04,
      "text": "It's very natural, very beautiful."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.04,
      "end": 232.04,
      "text": "Also the largest county in the UK."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.66,
      "end": 234.02,
      "text": "In northern England."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.28,
      "end": 236.74,
      "text": "And I've heard that Ben Akers, you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 237.08,
      "end": 237.78,
      "text": "Mr. Akers?"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.04,
      "end": 241.4,
      "text": "Yeah, he's from this town near here."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.68,
      "end": 243.12,
      "text": "Oh, he's from Yorkshire."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.22,
      "end": 245.28,
      "text": "Yeah, wow. How lucky he is."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.28,
      "end": 248.28,
      "text": "Mr. Akers, tell me about the pudding there."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.54,
      "end": 249.64,
      "text": "How's the pudding?"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.76,
      "end": 252.08,
      "text": "다면 만나면 한번 수다를 한번 떨어보세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 252.26,
      "end": 254.6,
      "text": "Ah, 예. 원조의 맛 궁금해요. 그 원조의 맛."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.7,
      "end": 256.78,
      "text": "그러게요. 자, 오늘 장면 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.78,
      "end": 278.34,
      "text": "둘 사이가 아직도 티격태격해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.34,
      "end": 280.78,
      "text": "Oh, and what are they doing now?"
    },
    {
      "start": 281.48,
      "end": 284.64,
      "text": "They're going into a place they're not supposed to go."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.82,
      "end": 285.22,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.58,
      "end": 285.98,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.12,
      "end": 287.3,
      "text": "That she was poking about."
    },
    {
      "start": 287.58,
      "end": 289.84,
      "text": "She pokes about all over the house."
    },
    {
      "start": 289.84,
      "end": 292.44,
      "text": "So, this room is off-limits."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.44,
      "end": 303.5,
      "text": "It's a very special room with pictures and items that belong to Mary's mother and Colin's mother, who were sisters, of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.64,
      "end": 309.66,
      "text": "So, it's full of their special items from their childhood and their past."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.66,
      "end": 313.54,
      "text": "그래요. 그런데 콜린이 별로 그렇게 좋아하는 것 같지는 않았어요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 313.76,
      "end": 319.46,
      "text": "No, Colin, he is very, let's say, he has scars about his mother."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.76,
      "end": 322.42,
      "text": "He wants to forget that part of his life."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.56,
      "end": 322.8,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.12,
      "end": 325.58,
      "text": "So, he has not overcome his past."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.68,
      "end": 326.36,
      "text": "Yeah, that's right."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.38,
      "end": 329.48,
      "text": "And he does not want to be reminded of his mom in any way."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.48,
      "end": 333.6,
      "text": "So, maybe he's in that room for a reason."
    },
    {
      "start": 333.9,
      "end": 334.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.16,
      "end": 335.4,
      "text": "He does not leave that room."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.4,
      "end": 335.72,
      "text": "Makes sense."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.98,
      "end": 338.1,
      "text": "Yeah, just like a hurtful memory of him."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.14,
      "end": 338.86,
      "text": "Very hurtful."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.16,
      "end": 339.94,
      "text": "Very painful."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.1,
      "end": 344.84,
      "text": "Yeah, 이제 조만간 이게 힐링이 되지 않을까 예상이 되지만,"
    },
    {
      "start": 345.06,
      "end": 348.78,
      "text": "오늘 들었던 장면을 위해서 미리 단어들을 알아볼게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.46,
      "end": 351.08,
      "text": "Something you need to see."
    },
    {
      "start": 351.28,
      "end": 352.9,
      "text": "Something you need to see."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.26,
      "end": 355.14,
      "text": "네가 봐야 할 뭔가야."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.48,
      "end": 355.92,
      "text": "라는 거죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.92,
      "end": 357.56,
      "text": "Hey, there's something you need to see."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.56,
      "end": 359.06,
      "text": "네가 봐야 할 게 뭔가가 있어."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.14,
      "end": 359.84,
      "text": "Follow me."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.94,
      "end": 360.9,
      "text": "빨리 따라와."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.98,
      "end": 361.42,
      "text": "라는 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.52,
      "end": 366.18,
      "text": "So, she takes him in the wheelchair and takes him to this room, this secret room."
    },
    {
      "start": 366.26,
      "end": 366.58,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.56,
      "end": 368.56,
      "text": "Take me back."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.68,
      "end": 370.06,
      "text": "네, take me back."
    },
    {
      "start": 370.18,
      "end": 370.98,
      "text": "무슨 의미일까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 371.66,
      "end": 373.02,
      "text": "날 다시 데려다줘."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.36,
      "end": 375.52,
      "text": "라고 하는 문맥에서 들린 표현입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 376.48,
      "end": 377.48,
      "text": "Don't be scared."
    },
    {
      "start": 377.6,
      "end": 380.3,
      "text": "네, 분명히 메리가 이렇게 이야기를 했을 거란 말이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.4,
      "end": 380.7,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.86,
      "end": 381.98,
      "text": "Don't be scared."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.4,
      "end": 383.32,
      "text": "두려워하지 마."
    },
    {
      "start": 383.66,
      "end": 384.16,
      "text": "라고 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 384.16,
      "end": 386.62,
      "text": "이 말 들으니까 더 두려워할 것 같은데요."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.62,
      "end": 387.82,
      "text": "She's frightened."
    },
    {
      "start": 388.2,
      "end": 388.5,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 388.7,
      "end": 389.14,
      "text": "Poor guy."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.34,
      "end": 389.5,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.8,
      "end": 391.0,
      "text": "이 내용 한 번 더 들어볼게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.38,
      "end": 394.0,
      "text": "I'm not taking you into the garden."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.76,
      "end": 396.39,
      "text": "There's something you need to see."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.07,
      "end": 398.65,
      "text": "I was three years old when your mother died."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.27,
